The paper discusses the estimation and debugging of the worst-case execution time (WCET) for real-time or safety-critical software, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) categories. The use of model checking as an analysis technique is also mentioned, which is a common topic in the formal methods (cs.AR) and embedded systems (cs.EM) categories. Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of analysis-friendly processors, which is relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) category.
